column12: yes, we obviously have to make some assumptions going forward in house prices and they are not that different than the assumptions you would see in most other that get published by case-shiller, etc. right now, they have a modest increase in home prices in 2013 and '14. i will stick with just those two years. but if it was 5% better than that, which is possible, that would run through our books in lower charge-offs and lower reserves. and just as a rule of thumb, $500 million for one year. it's a very rough rule of thumb.
